post_text:
Junior Turn In / Pick Day is Friday, May 22 from 9:00AM - 12:00PM.

To ensure that students are not liable for school equipment all summer and also to allow students the opportunity to pick up belongings in the school, we will be holding Underclassmen Turn-In Days. On these days students will do the following:
• Turn in School Chromebooks, Calculators, Library Books
• Textbooks and Uniforms
• Clean out their lockers

Directions: Please pull up to the front of the building using the student pick up route with all materials you need to turn in. A faculty member will take your materials while you stay in your
car. If you need to clean out your locker, please drop off your materials and then park. A faculty member will escort the student to and from their locker.

post_text:
The building might be closed, but the teachers at Alcoa High School are still working hard for our students. It's Teacher Appreciation Week and we need to let our teachers know we appreciate them and all that they do for our children. This year you can "adopt" a teacher. Click the link below and sign up for a teacher you wish to adopt (you can adopt more than one). By agreeing to adopt the teacher, you are agreeing to send them an email, a letter, or a small gift. Anything you can come up with to show them they are appreciated. It is our hope to get all teachers adopted! You have between now and May 15th to get this done. Let's show these great teachers some LOVE! If you have any questions, please contact Hope McDonald at hmcdonald@alcoaschools.net.
Here is the link: https://www.signupgenius.com/go/10C0444A8A62DA6FC1-teacher

post_text:
Alcoa City Schools will dismiss schools early this afternoon due to flooding conditions.

Buses will be picking up children on the following schedule:

Alcoa Elementary at 1 pm,

Alcoa Intermediate at 1:15,

Alcoa Middle at 1:30,

and Alcoa High School at 1:45.

Car riders can be picked up at the following times:

1:30 at Alcoa Elementary,

1:45 at Alcoa Intermediate,

2:00 at Alcoa Middle, and

2:15 at Alcoa High.

High school drivers will be dismissed at 2:15.

STARS will be closed today.

post_text: Help us beat Maryville in our annual canned food drive for Food Connection! We will be collecting cans and money from September 3rd - September 12th. $1 = 3 cans. The first period class that raises the most money/cans will receive a pizza party! Cans and money can be brought to the front office or to your 1st period teacher. On September 12th students will be able to pay $3 and get out of 3rd period. During 3rd Period we will have food trucks, face painting, and a dunking booth. Please make sure to bring money for these activities.

post_text:
The Tornado BBQ Tailgate Fundraiser will be held on Friday, August 30th and will take place directly across the football field at the end of the high school parking lot from 5-7:15 PM. The food for the tailgate will be provided by Smokin' Joes BBQ in Townsend, TN. The dinner plates will include a BBQ Pulled Pork Sandwich, Coleslaw, Chips, Dessert, and a drink. Tickets are $10, in which all of the proceeds will benefit our student-athletes and program.

It is our hope that many of you will join us for dinner prior to supporting our football team at the game! Many faculty and staff have already purchased a ticket from one of our players and we are very grateful for your support! We will take walk-ups next Friday, but would prefer if you purchase a ticket prior to next Friday to help us with an accurate count for the amount of food. Please email boys basketball head coach Ryan Collins at rcollins@alcoaschools.net if interested in purchasing tickets.

post_text: On Tuesday, October 30, AHS will run an abbreviated day schedule to accommodate seniors taking the ACT. Only seniors who registered to take the ACT on October 30 will report to school to test from 8:30 until 12:15. All buses will run at regular times, and we will serve breakfast and lunch. Any student not testing but present during 8:30 to 12:15 will be assigned a study hall in a teacher’s classroom. At 12:15, everyone will report to school, and every class will meet for a shortened class period.

Please be mindful of children, buses, and watch your speed in the schools zones. Also, a reminder of the law, enacted last year, in reference to cell phones in school zones. AHS STUDENT ORIENTATION
THURSDAY - JULY 19
Seniors (1-3pm)

FRIDAY - JULY 20
Freshmen (1-3pm), Sophomores (10-11am), Juniors (9-10am)

*Orientation process is 40 minutes. Students may show up anytime, during their allotted time. Parking passes may be purchased on these days and will be given on a 1st come, 1st serve basis.

*Those purchasing passes must bring copies of their driver's license & insurance & $25 to reserve spot.

*Tuition payments may be made during this time.

*Both tuition & parking payments may be made with cash, check or credit card. If paying with cash, please bring exact amount.
